    <!-- Founder Story -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-light">
        <div class="container mx-auto px-6">
            <h2 class="section-title text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-center">Our Founder's Story</h2>
            <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center">
                <div class="md:w-1/3 mb-8 md:mb-0 md:pr-8 text-center" data-aos="fade-right">
                    <div class="w-48 h-48 rounded-full overflow-hidden mx-auto mb-4 border-4 border-accent">
                        <img src="https://randomuser.me/api/portraits/men/76.jpg" alt="David Green, Founder" class="w-full h-full object-cover">
                    </div>
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-1">David Green</h3>
                    <p class="text-accent font-semibold mb-2">Founder & Lead Designer</p>
                </div>
                <div class="md:w-2/3" data-aos="fade-left">
                    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">David Green's journey began 15 years ago with a simple passion for plants and a belief that beautiful landscapes could coexist with environmental responsibility. After earning degrees in Landscape Architecture and Environmental Science, David worked with several landscaping firms before noticing a gap in the market for truly sustainable landscape design.</p>
                    
                    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">"I saw so many landscapes that looked great initially but required excessive water, chemicals, and maintenance to keep them that way," David explains. "I knew there had to be a better approach that could deliver both beauty and sustainability."</p>
                    
                    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">In 2010, David founded EverVerdant with a mission to create landscapes that thrive in their natural environment. Starting with just a small crew and a handful of clients willing to try a more eco-conscious approach, the company quickly developed a reputation for designs that remained beautiful throughout the seasons with minimal environmental impact.</p>
                    
                    <p class="text-gray-600">Today, EverVerdant has grown into a team of passionate professionals, but David's original vision remains at the heart of every project we undertake.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    
